mes but narrowly missed out on the podium each time.\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 1010, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He lost out on a medal by one-hundredth of a second in the biggest race in world sprinting just a week before.\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the fastest event of its type in history.\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tatjana Smith became the most decorated Olympian in South African historywith her haul oftwo medalsin Paris.\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1212, \"end\": 1220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999996544298171, \"rank\": 3.455701502814973e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1274, \"end\": 1279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5344902107189074e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She claimed gold in the 100m breaststroke and silver in the 200m event, an exact reversal of her antics in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1388, \"end\": 1393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7454499568666206, \"rank\": 0.34147166344861957, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The other Team SA medallists in 2024 areAlan Hatherly,who\\u00a0won bronze in the men's Mountain Bike (MTB) cross-country race, South Africa's first Olympic cycling medal since 1956, some 68 years ago, and the\\u00a0Rugby Sevens side,\\u00a0who claimed bronze by beating Australia.\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1410, \"end\": 1412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9012388917225895e-31, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1492, \"end\": 1495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mountain_bike\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5029179617645844e-12, \"text\": \"MTB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mountain_bike\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mountain_bike\"}, {\"begin\": 1517, \"end\": 1529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.742459467929768e-14, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1599, \"end\": 1611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\", \"score\": 0.9999999487868094, \"rank\": 5.121336784325468e-08, \"text\": \"Rugby Sevens\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\"}, {\"begin\": 1648, \"end\": 1657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999918763294597, \"rank\": 7.71472092207273e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 4x100m relay side and Jo-Ane van Dyk's silver in the women's javelin took Team SA's totalmedal tally to SIX.A gold, three silvers and two bronzes.\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1685, \"end\": 1699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jo-Ane van Dyk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\"}, {\"begin\": 1742, \"end\": 1744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9012388917225895e-31, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Outside of a South African perspective, there were so many stellar performances to cherish in Paris.\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1905, \"end\": 1910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5344902107189074e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"21-year-oldLetsile Tebogo's win in the 200m finalwas the first gold medal in Botswana's history at the games.\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 2021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1989, \"end\": 1997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.4960629134373546e-12, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was also the fifth-fastest time in the history of the event, not only at the Olympics but anywhere on the planet.\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Legendary American gymnast Simone Biles claimed three golds and a silver, taking her overall medal tally at the Olympic Games to 11 (seven gold, two silver, two bronze) across three editions.\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2149, \"end\": 2157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999832112529994, \"rank\": 1.677517512210018e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2166, \"end\": 2178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the pool, French golden boy Leon Marchand, still only 22 years old, won four golds and a bronze.\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2344, \"end\": 2350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.6298316953268248, \"rank\": 0.49834097226128515, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2367, \"end\": 2375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9870937434413413, \"rank\": 0.013007710375073521, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like Tebogo, we will see more of him in 2028 and beyond.\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch distance runner Sifan Hassan did the unthinkable by winning bronze over 5000m and 10000m and then entering the marathon on the final day of the games.\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2489, \"end\": 2494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9953653605786108, \"rank\": 0.0025524083054877756, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 2511, \"end\": 2523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sifan Hassan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won that in an Olympic record time (2:22:55), just for good measure.\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2718, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was easily one of the greatest marathons in the history of the games; the top three separated by only 15 seconds.\", \"from\": 2719, \"to\": 2835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ethiopia's Tigst Assefa was only three seconds behind Hassan in a sprint finish to claim silver.\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 2932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2836, \"end\": 2844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9998689468291965, \"rank\": 0.0001310703326773526, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cian Oldknow (32nd) was the best South African performer in a superb time of 2:30:29.\", \"from\": 2933, \"to\": 3018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2933, \"end\": 2937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cian\", \"score\": 0.9999999141782646, \"rank\": 8.58216620474824e-08, \"text\": \"Cian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Irvette van Zyl\\u00a0finished\\u00a037th\\u00a0in\\u00a02:31:14, and the legendary Gerda Steyn finished 45th with a time of 2:32:51.\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3019, \"end\": 3034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvette_van_Zyl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Irv